</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="591" pageNumber="592">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1924" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Amara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="591" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microcephala">Amara microcephala</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1924: 62. Type locality: &quot;Southern Pines [Moore County], North Carolina&quot; (original citation). Lectotype (♂), designated by Lindroth (1975: 136), in USNM [# 47293]. Synonymy established by Hieke (1994: 337).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="591" pageNumber="592">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1924" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Amara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="591" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recticollis">Amara recticollis</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1924: 62. Type locality: &quot;Southern Pines [Moore County], North Carolina&quot; (original citation). Holotype [by monotypy] (♂) in USNM [# 47291]. Synonymy established by Hieke (1994: 337).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="592" pageNumber="593" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="592" pageNumber="593">
<pageBreakToken pageId="592" pageNumber="593" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="592" pageNumber="593">This species ranges from southern Quebec to southeastern Alberta, south to southern Arizona, southern Texas, west-central Alabama, and North Carolina (Hieke 2000: 76-79).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
