<subSubSection pageId="592" pageNumber="593" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="592" pageNumber="593">
Lindroth (1968: 730) regarded this form as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Amara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="592" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Amara littoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mannerheim but Hieke (1994: 337) considered it as a valid species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
